==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mummery
<hw>Mum"mer*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Mummeries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>momerie</ets>, of
Dutch or German origin. See <er>Mumm</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Masking; frolic in disguise; buffoonery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>mummery</qex> of foreign strollers.</q>
<rj><qau>Fenton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Farcical show; hypocritical disguise and parade or
ceremonies.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mummichog</ent>⟦br⟧
